This paper is about natural language generation (NLG) from structured data using neural networks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses various techniques for improving the NLG process, such as attention mechanisms and ensembling, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper evaluates the quality of generated text using automated metrics and human evaluation, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
